If you have an old pastebin key to a story that is no longer up and you don't know the title of the story you can use ( https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Azuhmier/hmofa/master/code/json/gitIo.json ) to convert the 8 character paste key to a 'gitio' url where it is being archived. Or you can take your 8 character paste key and append it to the following string: 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Azuhmier/hmofa/master/archive_7/'

SUMMARY
Paste_Url = https://pastebin.com/xDXtKwbs
Paste_Key = xDXtKwbs

1) gitIo.json
>go to https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Azuhmier/hmofa/master/code/json/gitIo.json
>ctrl + f 'Paste_Key'
>copy the git.io url
>https://git.io/J3MzJ

2) append archive url
> 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Azuhmier/hmofa/master/archive_7/' + Paste_key
> https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Azuhmier/hmofa/master/archive_7/xDXtKwbs

Practice for the sake of practice has never been something I've enjoyed or done a lot of. It's one of the reasons I don't like to call myself an artist.
